ometer isolates target photons with high signal-to-noise. TOMCAT design\nis discussed, including target optimization, system geometry, and scan\nprocedures. Features which are 160 nm wide are resolved in three-dimensional\nimages on a Cu-SiO$_2$ IC sample, demonstrating the capabilities of\nlaboratory-scale nanotomography based on a focused electron beam and TES\nspectrometer.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Dec 2022 19:05:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-22"}
