 of quantum\n$\\mathfrak{sl}_2$ on both sides of the equivalence, and answer a question by\nCrivelli, Felder, and Wieczerkowski. We also make sure that the restriction of\nthese representations to the Torelli group $\\mathcal{I}(\\varSigma_{g,1})$ are\nintegral, in the sense that the actions have coefficients in the ring of\ncyclotomic integers $\\mathbb{Z}[\\zeta]$, when expressed in these bases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Dec 2022 11:29:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 8 Mar 2023 18:31:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-09"}
